  paragraphs:
  - Stop!
  - Great heavens! Who are you?
  - Those items, all that you have just taken...they are not yours to take!
  - 'Don''t be alarmed. I''m simply collecting specimens for educational purposes.

'
  - What you have taken from here belongs to my people, not you! Please return them
    at once!
  - 'Surely you understand the importance of preserving your culture for future generations? '
  - I'm afraid I must decline..these pieces will help educate people about your heritage.
  - The forest will not let you leave with stolen goods...it watches closely and
    always remembers.
  - What could you possibly mean? You speak nonsense.
  - I must take my leave now. Science waits for no one, I'm afraid.
  - You have made your choice, traveler.  You shall soon reap wat you have sown.
